CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 9, 1946, pg. 17 reads: "In YMCA Drive - Urban Williams, standing, general secretary of the YMCA of Pittsburgh, lauded the Centre Avenue branch for its efforts in the 1946 membership campaign. P.L. Prattis, general chairman, sparked the drive to within hailing distance of the goal of $5,000.  The drive has been extended for one more week in an attempt to exceed the quota. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Urban Williams and P. L. Prattis, gathered at table with trophies in front of toteboard for Centre Avenue YMCA membership campaign banquet
